Greek Euro Exit Is Possible, Seehofer Tells Bild

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-09-07T05:44:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/greek-exit-from-euro-is-possible-seehofer-tells-bild.html
(Corrects name of Seehofer’s party.)  Greece’s exit from the euro is
possible,  Horst Seehofer , head of Germany’s Christian Social
Union that’s in a governing coalition with Chancellor Angela Merkel’s Christian Democratic Union, said in an  interview  with
Bild today.  “I don’t rule it out, but I am confident that the chosen
way of aid and savings efforts will be successful,” he told the
newspaper. Seehofer is also prime minister of Bavaria.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 